---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title="About Us" description="Who we are and how we work" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />

    <header class="page-hero">
      <h1>About Us</h1>
      <p>Personalized essay consulting led by Kristine &amp; Joseph.</p>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="about">
        <!-- Row 1 -->
        <div class="row">
          <img src="/JHY.png" alt="Introducing Joseph Yim" class="photo" />
          <div class="copy">
            <h2>Joseph Yim</h2>
            <p>
              For nearly fifteen years, Joseph Yim has taught writing in hagwons, English camps, and private settingsâ€”helping students turn ideas into essays that are genuine, structured, and impactful. Drawing on his background in sociology from UC Berkeley and law from Harvard Law School, he teaches students to think critically about audience, diction, tone, and structureâ€”approaching writing as both art and system. Having guided more than seventy students through college and graduate applications, Joseph encourages honest thinking over fancy words and helps writers express complex ideas simply, beautifully, and with purpose.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Row 2 -->
        <div class="row row-reverse">
          <div class="copy">
            <h2>Kristine Ma</h2>
            <p>
              Kristine has over a decade of experience teaching and mentoring students in STEM, test preparation, and college applications. She holds a bachelorâ€™s degree in Chemistry from the University of Chicago, a masterâ€™s in Biomedical Engineering from Brown University, and a Ph.D. in Bioengineering from Northeastern University. A former certified high school teacher, Kristine has taught Chemistry, General Science, and SAT/ACT subjects, and coached award-winning Science Olympiad and engineering teamsâ€”including a state champion team that advanced to the national TEAMS competition. She has also taught at The Princeton Review (Seoul, Korea) and mentored university students in research and thesis development as a Post-Doctoral Research Scholar at Arizona State Universityâ€™s School of Engineering. Known for her adaptive teaching style and thoughtful rigor, Kristine focuses on maximizing each studentâ€™s potential.
            </p>
          </div>
          <img src="/KYM.png" alt="Introducing Kristine Ma" class="photo" />
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <style>
      /* Hero */
      .page-hero {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3rem;
        background: #fafafa;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
      }
      .page-hero h1 {
        font-size: 2.8rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin: 0 0 .75rem;
      }
      .page-hero p {
        color: #555;
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        margin: 0;
      }

      /* About section */
      .about {
        max-width: 1900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 4rem;
      }

      .row {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 3rem;
        align-items: center;
        margin-bottom: 6rem;
      }

      /* Desktop layout */
      @media (min-width: 900px) {
        .row {
          grid-template-columns: 72% 28%; /* text wider */
        }
        .row-reverse {
          grid-template-columns: 28% 72%;
          direction: rtl;
        }
        .row-reverse > * {
          direction: ltr;
        }
      }

      .photo {
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 340px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,.08);
        display: block;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      .copy {
        max-width: 1100px; /* wider text container */
      }
      .copy h2 {
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        font-size: 2rem;
        font-weight: 700;
      }
      .copy p {
        color: #333;
        line-height: 1.9;
        font-size: 1.15rem; /* ðŸ’¥ larger font size */
        letter-spacing: 0.02rem;
        margin: 0;
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
